@node strnlen
@section @code{strnlen}---character string length
@findex strnlen
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <string.h>
size_t strnlen(const char *@var{str}, size_t @var{n});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
The @code{strnlen} function works out the length of the string
starting at @code{*@var{str}} by counting chararacters until it
reaches a NUL character or the maximum: @var{n} number of
characters have been inspected.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
@code{strnlen} returns the character count or @var{n}.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{strnlen} is a GNU extension.

@code{strnlen} requires no supporting OS subroutines.


@*
